{"questionId":"33373910","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider a cylinder of radius 4<em>r</em> and height <em>h</em>. A smaller cylinder of radius <em>r</em> is removed from the centre to form a hollow cylinder. This is shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p>All lengths are measured in centimetres.</p>\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 420 230\" role=\"img\" aria-label=\"A hollow cylinder with outer radius 4r, inner radius r, and height h\" style=\"max-width:420px;width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;\">\n  <defs>\n    <marker id=\"arrow\" markerWidth=\"8\" markerHeight=\"8\" refX=\"4\" refY=\"4\" orient=\"auto\" markerUnits=\"strokeWidth\"><path d=\"M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"/></marker>\n  </defs>\n  <ellipse cx=\"210\" cy=\"54\" rx=\"118\" ry=\"34\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <ellipse cx=\"210\" cy=\"54\" rx=\"31\" ry=\"10\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <path d=\"M92 54 L92 164\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <path d=\"M328 54 L328 164\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <path d=\"M179 54 L179 164\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\" stroke-dasharray=\"5 6\"/>\n  <path d=\"M241 54 L241 164\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\" stroke-dasharray=\"5 6\"/>\n  <ellipse cx=\"210\" cy=\"164\" rx=\"118\" ry=\"34\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <ellipse cx=\"210\" cy=\"164\" rx=\"31\" ry=\"10\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <line x1=\"350\" y1=\"54\" x2=\"350\" y2=\"164\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" marker-start=\"url(#arrow)\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\"/>\n  <text x=\"365\" y=\"113\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"currentColor\">h</text>\n  <line x1=\"210\" y1=\"164\" x2=\"241\" y2=\"164\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" marker-start=\"url(#arrow)\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\"/>\n  <text x=\"219\" y=\"194\" font-size=\"22\" fill=\"currentColor\">r</text>\n  <line x1=\"241\" y1=\"164\" x2=\"328\" y2=\"164\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" marker-start=\"url(#arrow)\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\"/>\n  <text x=\"276\" y=\"194\" font-size=\"22\" fill=\"currentColor\">3r</text>\n  <text x=\"136\" y=\"216\" font-size=\"15\" fill=\"currentColor\">diagram not to scale</text>\n</svg>\n<p>The total surface area of the hollow cylinder, in cm<sup>2</sup>, is given by <em>S</em>.</p>\n<p>The volume of the hollow cylinder, in cm<sup>3</sup>, is given by <em>V</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The total surface area of the hollow cylinder is 240&pi; cm<sup>2</sup>.</p>\n<p>From part (b), <em>V</em> = 360&pi;<em>r</em> - 45&pi;<em>r</em><sup>3</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The hollow cylinder has its maximum volume when <em>r</em> = <em>p</em>&radic;(2/3), where <em>p</em> &isin; Z<sup>+</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, find this maximum volume, giving your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute their value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math> &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>720</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>240</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>480</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>480</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33373910","referenceCode":"24N.1.SL.TZ2.9e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, find this maximum volume, giving your answer in the form qπ23, where q∈ℤ+.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
